```javascript
function factorial(n) {
    if (n === 1) { // Base case
        return 1;
    } else {
        return n * factorial(n - 1); // Recursive call
    }
}
```

This function calls itself, reducing `n` by one and multiplying the result until it reached n=1. It's the essence of recursion: breaking down a problem into smaller instances of itself. This will work for any non-negative integer you pass to it. To understand how it works, try tracing its execution step-by-step with different inputs.

